📌 Gender Classification API

A simple backend API that classifies a name by gender using the Genderize API, processes the response, and returns a structured result with confidence evaluation.

🚀 Base URL
genderizeapicall-production.up.railway.app
📍 Endpoint
GET /api/classify?name={name}

Classifies a given name and returns processed gender prediction data.

✅ Example Request
GET /api/classify?name=samuel
📦 Success Response (200 OK)
{
  "status":"success",
  "data":{"name":"samuel",
  "gender":"male",
  "probability":0.99,
  "sample_size":603089,
  "is_confident":true,
  "processed_at":"2026-04-16T14:51:27.952Z"
  }
}
❌ Error Responses
400 Bad Request

Missing or empty name parameter

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Name query parameter is required"
}
422 Unprocessable Entity

Invalid input or no prediction available

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "No prediction available for the provided name"
}
502 Bad Gateway

External API failure

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Failed to fetch data from external API"
}
⚙️ Processing Logic
Extracts:
gender
probability
count → renamed to sample_size
Computes:
is_confident:
true if:
probability ≥ 0.7 AND
sample_size ≥ 100
otherwise false
Generates:
processed_at: Current UTC timestamp in ISO 8601 format
⚠️ Edge Case Handling

If the external API returns:

gender: null OR
count: 0

The API responds with:

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "No prediction available for the provided name"
}
🌐 CORS

CORS is enabled:

Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
🛠 Tech Stack
Node.js
Express.js
Axios
CORS
▶️ Running Locally
npm install
node index.js

Server runs on:

https://genderizeapicall-production.up.railway.app/
🧪 Testing

Example:

https://genderizeapicall-production.up.railway.app/api/classify?name=samuel


📌 Notes
Response time optimized (excluding external API latency)
Handles multiple concurrent requests
Input is normalized (trimmed and lowercase)